rComments: If you get to ESP2992 strongly suggest taking her. She is great! She loves teaching language and culture. She keeps lecture interesting and everyone engaged. She is clear on what she expects of you. Follow any instructions she gives you and you ll do fine. You will get a lot of feedback and learn a lot!
Truly outstanding- she is always available and helpful. A joy to learn from.

She teaches on behalf of Luis Abanto. She's exceptional. Explains really well and she's easy to understand. She's so caring. But she does requires to student to participate in class. The syllabus is not organized and clear at all.

Great professor! She is really organized, knowledgeable, helpful and understanding. She encouraged participation and made us feel comfortable to share our opinions and ask questions. She also gives clear feedback. I loved class activities, like the Kahoot quiz on Spanish idiomatic expressions.

Literally the most caring Spanish prof I've had in my undergrad. She was always available to meet with students to review what was learned it class or simply to practice speaking Spanish, even outside of her office hours. Make sure to participate in class and don't hesitate to ask to meet with her if you have any doubts. 10/10 recommend this prof!

Mara es una profesora increíble. Hace dos años que era mi profesora y cada vez era simpática y muy generosa. Con ella puedo hablar sin estrés que vaya juzgarme, ella comprende que somos estudiantes y aprendemos aún. No es un curso difícil pero tendréis que participar mucho, venir en clase y hacer todos los ejercicios si queréis sacar buena nota.
